OL,6,FWhat is Uppies and Downies?
OL,8,FThe Uppies, from the top of the town,
OL,9,Fand Downies, from the bottom of the
OL,10,Ftown, face off against each other.
OL,12,FThe object is to "hail the ball" at
OL,13,Fthe opposing team's goal.
OL,15,FHailing the ball involves throwing it
OL,16,Fthree times in the air. The Downies'
OL,17,Fgoal is a capstan on the Prince of
OL,18,FWales' dock, while the Uppies' is the
OL,19,Fgates of Workington Hall in Curwen
OL,20,FPark.
